1
00:01:00,978 --> 00:01:04,981
Law and The City

2
00:01:04,982 --> 00:01:09,987
CHARACTERS, ORGANIZATIONS, EVENTS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

3
00:01:40,267 --> 00:01:43,020
SEOUL NAT'L UNIV OF EDUCATION STATION

4
00:01:44,688 --> 00:01:46,647
<i>This stop is
Seoul Nat'l Univ. of Education.</i>

5
00:01:46,648 --> 00:01:48,900
- Excuse me.
<i>- Court and Prosecutors' Office.</i>

6
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:51,695
<i>The doors are on your right.</i>

7
00:01:53,030 --> 00:01:56,449
<i>Passengers headed toward Daehwa,
Gupabal, or Ogeum Stations...</i>

8
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:59,202
<i>Here, we have a man.</i>

9
00:02:10,922 --> 00:02:12,799
<i>A black suit and a white shirt.</i>

10
00:02:13,925 --> 00:02:16,970
<i>Judging from his face,
he slept with his tie on last night.</i>

11
00:02:17,679 --> 00:02:20,848
<i>His commute takes him 30 minutes
by subway on Line 3,</i>

12
00:02:20,849 --> 00:02:23,810
<i>but he appears exhausted,
as if it were a three-year trek.</i>

13
00:02:24,936 --> 00:02:26,187
<i>Dozing from fatigue,</i>

14
00:02:26,188 --> 00:02:29,191
<i>he still wakes up a station
before his stop like a professional.</i>

15
00:02:34,363 --> 00:02:37,657
<i>His office is in Seocho-dong,
where there are more law firms</i>

16
00:02:37,658 --> 00:02:39,116
<i>than restaurants.</i>

17
00:02:39,117 --> 00:02:41,035
SEOUL NAT'L UNIV OF EDUCATION

18
00:02:41,036 --> 00:02:44,122
<i>He has the spirit
of a worn-out office worker who'd say,</i>

19
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:47,750
<i>"We all carry resignation letters
in our hearts."</i>

20
00:02:47,751 --> 00:02:49,169
Damn, it's freezing.

21
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:53,382
<i>But he does everything asked of him
and never complains.</i>

22
00:02:53,965 --> 00:02:55,467
<i>A textbook employee.</i>

23
00:02:57,969 --> 00:03:00,805
<i>In Seocho-dong,
where most don't last five years</i>

24
00:03:00,806 --> 00:03:04,518
<i>and go solo or become in-house counsel,
he's about to break the record.</i>

25
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:11,066
<i>His workday stretches on forever,
but he always punches in on time.</i>

26
00:03:11,608 --> 00:03:14,694
<i>He's a salaried associate attorney
in his ninth year.</i>

27
00:03:14,695 --> 00:03:17,406
ASSOCIATE
A LAWYER AND AN EMPLOYEE OF A LAW FIRM

28
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:21,201
<i>He steps into the elevator
of Hyungmin Building</i>

29
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:24,204
<i>yearning for the far-off time
to clock out.</i>

30
00:03:26,289 --> 00:03:28,333
<i>He lets out a sigh as short as a yawn.</i>

31
00:03:33,839 --> 00:03:35,005
You're here early.

32
00:03:35,006 --> 00:03:37,842
At this moment,
the man speaks to someone.

33
00:03:37,843 --> 00:03:40,345
Doesn't all that talking this early
wear you out?

34
00:03:43,265 --> 00:03:45,934
I talk because I'm tired.

35
00:03:46,810 --> 00:03:48,811
Hey. I barely dragged myself out

36
00:03:48,812 --> 00:03:50,771
- for a morning meeting.
- Later.

37
00:03:50,772 --> 00:03:53,732
On my way here,
I got a text saying it's delayed. When?

38
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,818
At 8:35 a.m.

39
00:03:55,819 --> 00:03:57,153
People have no manners.

40
00:03:57,154 --> 00:03:59,364
Like you, Juhyeong,
who asks and just leaves!

41
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:04,452
LAW GROUP KYUNGMIN

42
00:04:04,453 --> 00:04:06,538
- Good morning.
- Hello.

43
00:04:07,414 --> 00:04:08,457
Good morning, sir.

44
00:04:10,834 --> 00:04:13,545
ATTORNEY AHN JUHYEONG

45
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:47,871
Man, I don't want to do this.

46
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:05,847
Hi.

47
00:05:10,894 --> 00:05:13,230
How about looking with your eyes open?

48
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:15,648
- When did you get home?
- 2:00 a.m.

49
00:05:15,649 --> 00:05:19,277
Hey! Good morning, everybody.

50
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:21,487
You waltzed out without a briefcase?

51
00:05:21,488 --> 00:05:23,740
I got here earlier.

52
00:05:25,492 --> 00:05:28,744
I had a meeting this morning,
so I barely dragged myself out.

53
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:30,789
But I got a text saying it was delayed.

54
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:36,044
When? At 8:35 a.m.

55
00:05:37,504 --> 00:05:39,798
People have no manners.

56
00:05:40,966 --> 00:05:44,344
There are three of us here,
and Sanggi only presses his floor.

57
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:48,222
<i>People like you...</i>

58
00:05:48,223 --> 00:05:50,266
<i>I'll press it for you next time</i>

59
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:51,892
<i>All talk, as usual</i>

60
00:05:51,893 --> 00:05:54,061
<i>Better than nothing at all</i>

61
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,146
Geez.

62
00:05:57,274 --> 00:06:00,192
- Is today Munjeong's trial?
- She wouldn't be here yet either way.

63
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:01,694
That is true.

64
00:06:01,695 --> 00:06:02,820
I'm off!

65
00:06:02,821 --> 00:06:04,822
Right! What should we have for lunch?

66
00:06:04,823 --> 00:06:07,700
Munjeong said she wanted
bean sprout soup yesterday.

67
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:10,035
What are we going to eat?

68
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,620
See you later on the fifth floor!

69
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:14,081
Changwon's so upbeat
this early in the morning.

70
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:15,165
SELL

71
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:17,209
So chaotic.

72
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:18,753
And nice!

73
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:21,547
- Did you profit?
- I did.

74
00:06:21,548 --> 00:06:23,216
- How much?
- 8,800 won.

75
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:43,485
The defendant did not murder the victim.

76
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:47,240
The real perpetrator
was a third person at the scene.

77
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:50,076
<i>Your Honor!</i>

78
00:06:50,744 --> 00:06:52,746
<i>The defendant did not murder the victim.</i>

79
00:06:53,913 --> 00:06:55,332
At the time of the incident,

80
00:06:55,832 --> 00:06:57,458
rather than the victim or defendant

81
00:06:57,459 --> 00:07:00,754
the real perpetrator
was a third person at the scene.

82
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:04,257
There's a witness outside the door...

83
00:07:06,301 --> 00:07:07,552
who can reveal all of this.

84
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:22,942
Nice.

85
00:07:29,407 --> 00:07:31,576
FIRST-YEAR ATTORNEY

86
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:37,874
Hello.

87
00:07:41,211 --> 00:07:43,420
SECOND YEAR

88
00:07:43,421 --> 00:07:45,715
I'm just so frustrated.

89
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:48,176
I didn't hit anyone.

90
00:07:49,803 --> 00:07:51,346
All I did was get hit.

91
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:55,183
This is so unfair!

92
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:57,435
Seriously...

93
00:07:59,562 --> 00:08:01,272
This is so unfair.

94
00:08:34,222 --> 00:08:35,724
THIRD YEAR

95
00:08:43,773 --> 00:08:45,942
I'm not suing for the money.

96
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:49,486
That young man behaved so badly.

97
00:08:49,487 --> 00:08:51,614
It's just to teach him
some life experience,

98
00:08:52,282 --> 00:08:54,241
so feel free to take it easy.

99
00:08:54,242 --> 00:08:56,745
Still, you should get paid
for what you're owed.

100
00:08:58,288 --> 00:08:59,455
Gosh, no need.

101
00:08:59,456 --> 00:09:00,957
I don't want that money.

102
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:07,713
Look at this, Your Honor.

103
00:09:07,714 --> 00:09:09,841
How could anyone pay for this?

104
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:14,470
Hey, how could you lose?

105
00:09:14,471 --> 00:09:16,221
You told me not to worry!

106
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:18,724
I needed to get that money, you bastard!

107
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:21,060
We couldn't win with a product like that.

108
00:09:21,061 --> 00:09:22,686
What did you say, you bastard?

109
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:24,772
- You son of a...
- Sir!

110
00:09:24,773 --> 00:09:26,816
Sir! Please!

111
00:09:48,171 --> 00:09:51,883
EIGHTH-YEAR ATTORNEY

112
00:09:55,929 --> 00:09:57,971
- This is delicious.
- That's right.

113
00:09:57,972 --> 00:09:59,933
Another bottle of soju, please!

114
00:10:00,975 --> 00:10:02,101
This is good.

115
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:04,645
Ma'am, over here. More meat, please.

116
00:10:04,646 --> 00:10:06,231
Here's your chicken feet.

117
00:10:07,023 --> 00:10:08,316
NINTH YEAR

118
00:10:19,744 --> 00:10:22,539
<i>In court, I must stand by my client.</i>

119
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:25,625
<i>But that doesn't mean
I have to be their friend.</i>

120
00:10:26,668 --> 00:10:28,920
It took me nine years to figure that out.

121
00:10:36,136 --> 00:10:37,262
TODAY'S CASES

122
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:55,238
Let's go!

123
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:04,789
Your Honor.

124
00:11:05,373 --> 00:11:08,251
There's a witness outside the door
who can reveal all of this.

125
00:11:09,085 --> 00:11:10,086
Your Honor.

126
00:11:10,837 --> 00:11:13,256
I'd like to call a witness on this matter.

127
00:11:18,011 --> 00:11:20,012
We'll proceed with the next case.

128
00:11:20,013 --> 00:11:22,682
Civil case number 2024-3923.

129
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:33,151
Who's representing the plaintiff?

130
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:37,197
I'm Ahn Juhyeong with Law Group Kyungmin,
attorney for the plaintiff.

131
00:11:40,658 --> 00:11:43,244
Yes, that part was stated
in the previous preparations.

132
00:11:44,746 --> 00:11:46,039
Your Honor!

133
00:11:51,586 --> 00:11:52,754
Your Honor?

134
00:11:55,340 --> 00:11:57,717
Please sit down
and speak into the microphone.

135
00:11:58,968 --> 00:12:00,010
Yes, Your Honor.

136
00:12:00,011 --> 00:12:02,096
DEFENDANT, PLAINTIFF

137
00:12:09,479 --> 00:12:10,646
I, the counsel--

138
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:13,107
You're the attorney
for the defendant, correct?

139
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:15,568
Yes.

140
00:12:16,527 --> 00:12:18,362
I, the...

141
00:12:18,363 --> 00:12:21,532
I, the counsel, would like to call...

142
00:12:23,243 --> 00:12:24,827
a witness on this matter.

143
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:45,056
Okay, please go back
and submit the witness application.

144
00:12:47,016 --> 00:12:48,059
What?

145
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:50,478
But...

146
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:54,773
- The witness is here today in person.
- So?

147
00:12:54,774 --> 00:12:57,402
There's no stenographer, no time.
Nothing's ready.

148
00:12:59,404 --> 00:13:00,946
Your Honor!

149
00:13:00,947 --> 00:13:04,450
Then, may I at least explain
the purpose of the witness request?

150
00:13:09,539 --> 00:13:12,124
I have dozens of hearings
to get through just today.

151
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:14,668
Even if you explain it now,
I won't remember it.

152
00:13:14,669 --> 00:13:16,087
Submit it in writing.

153
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:21,967
The next hearing
will be on January 14th at 4:00 p.m.

154
00:13:21,968 --> 00:13:23,094
Is that okay?

155
00:13:23,886 --> 00:13:25,470
The plaintiff's counsel agrees.

156
00:13:25,471 --> 00:13:26,681
And the defense counsel?

157
00:13:28,057 --> 00:13:29,100
What?

158
00:13:31,561 --> 00:13:34,314
Right. I'm sorry. One second, please.

159
00:13:37,191 --> 00:13:38,358
What day was that again?

160
00:13:38,359 --> 00:13:40,361
- The 14th.
- The 14th...

161
00:13:43,531 --> 00:13:46,659
Yes, I believe I'm available as well.

162
00:13:58,129 --> 00:13:59,547
I'm sorry, sir.

163
00:14:04,635 --> 00:14:07,804
Don't learn how to defend cases
from TV shows.

164
00:14:07,805 --> 00:14:10,016
Come early
and study the earlier hearings.

165
00:14:11,434 --> 00:14:12,769
Okay. Thank you.

166
00:14:13,478 --> 00:14:16,230
No one's ever pointed that out before.

167
00:14:16,814 --> 00:14:18,440
I didn't say that to be thanked.

168
00:14:18,441 --> 00:14:20,818
It's because you dragged this trial out.

169
00:14:23,738 --> 00:14:27,491
Besides, that show's about criminal cases.
This is a civil case.

170
00:14:27,492 --> 00:14:28,951
At least watch the right show.

171
00:14:42,298 --> 00:14:44,592
I'll get it all ready
and mail it to you.

172
00:14:49,013 --> 00:14:50,348
Okay.

173
00:14:50,848 --> 00:14:51,849
What?

174
00:14:52,391 --> 00:14:55,186
No, I'm on the subway.

175
00:14:55,978 --> 00:14:57,271
It's unusually quiet today.

176
00:14:58,606 --> 00:15:00,190
- Anyway--
- Try to be on time.

177
00:15:00,191 --> 00:15:01,691
Yes, sir!

178
00:15:01,692 --> 00:15:02,860
Yes, yes.

179
00:15:07,490 --> 00:15:08,616
Right?

180
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:12,703
- Attorney Ahn, you're late.
- Hey!

181
00:15:26,843 --> 00:15:30,096
These are last week's rulings
on the Tech Kori case

182
00:15:31,222 --> 00:15:33,099
and the Seoul General case.

183
00:15:33,683 --> 00:15:35,268
You won both cases.

184
00:15:36,102 --> 00:15:37,812
- Congratulations!
- Thank you.

185
00:15:41,274 --> 00:15:44,235
This one's the ruling
on Park Jeongeun's case.

186
00:15:44,819 --> 00:15:46,862
You lost this one.

187
00:15:46,863 --> 00:15:48,406
Okay, thank you.

188
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:57,832
Mr. Na wanted you to take
a consultation on an assault case.

189
00:15:58,291 --> 00:15:59,292
Now?

190
00:16:00,543 --> 00:16:02,962
Yes, are you busy?

191
00:16:05,715 --> 00:16:07,632
No, orders are orders.

192
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:08,759
I'll be right there.

193
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:13,763
ATTORNEY AHN JUHYEONG

194
00:16:13,764 --> 00:16:15,349
MANAGING PARTNER
NA KYUNGMIN

195
00:16:25,568 --> 00:16:27,110
Attorney Ahn treats me the same.

196
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:29,447
Don't mind him.
He gets the job done though.

197
00:16:33,618 --> 00:16:38,414
Do lawyers usually not care
about winning or losing?

198
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:44,085
Goddamn it!

199
00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:45,170
CASE DENIED

200
00:16:45,171 --> 00:16:46,297
This sucks.

201
00:16:50,218 --> 00:16:51,384
Yes.

202
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:52,802
Yes, please proceed.

203
00:16:52,803 --> 00:16:54,013
Okay, thank you.

204
00:16:58,476 --> 00:16:59,477
Hello?

205
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:01,062
Yes, put him through.

206
00:17:03,064 --> 00:17:04,482
Attorney Yu Dongwook speaking.

207
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:19,121
Good luck, sir.

208
00:17:23,584 --> 00:17:25,001
Please go over these too.

209
00:17:25,002 --> 00:17:27,004
- Ma'am--
- Can you do it by tonight?

210
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:28,923
Okay, then. Tomorrow night.

211
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:34,387
For goodness' sake.

212
00:17:43,312 --> 00:17:45,730
Busy, right?
I told them to throw in a bonus.

213
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:48,025
You'll get it soon. Going somewhere?

214
00:17:52,113 --> 00:17:53,656
LAW OFFICE HOJEON 1 MILLION WON

215
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:57,033
By tonight?

216
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:58,201
By lunch.

217
00:17:58,202 --> 00:17:59,287
Okay.

218
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:15,386
- Attorney Cho, take this consultation.
- Right now?

219
00:18:16,304 --> 00:18:18,054
I have a meeting in 10 minutes.

220
00:18:18,055 --> 00:18:19,849
You can finish in 10 minutes, then.

221
00:18:20,433 --> 00:18:23,144
It's likely just another drifter
from the streets of Seocho.

222
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:25,563
If they won't hire, walk out.

223
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:29,734
What?

224
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:33,446
I understand, sir.

225
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:40,369
He's always dumping grunt work on me.

226
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:47,960
Is there any way you could make it work?

227
00:18:50,671 --> 00:18:53,007
Well, it's just that...

228
00:18:55,384 --> 00:18:59,180
This is our community leader.

229
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:03,683
She always comes with me
to my consultations.

230
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:08,481
I'm telling you
she's great at reading people.

231
00:19:11,692 --> 00:19:12,943
Sir.

232
00:19:13,444 --> 00:19:14,445
Yes?

233
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:20,033
You have such great energy.

234
00:19:20,034 --> 00:19:21,118
Is that so?

235
00:19:21,702 --> 00:19:24,830
You have a face full of fortune.

236
00:19:25,748 --> 00:19:27,040
Let him handle the case.

237
00:19:27,041 --> 00:19:28,876
You'll definitely win.

238
00:19:29,794 --> 00:19:31,211
My goodness!

239
00:19:31,212 --> 00:19:34,589
She said we'll definitely win, sir!

240
00:19:34,590 --> 00:19:36,050
Wait, but...

241
00:19:37,468 --> 00:19:40,262
What makes you say I have good energy?

242
00:19:41,097 --> 00:19:45,434
I've often heard I have nice ears.
Would you like to take a look?

243
00:19:55,111 --> 00:19:56,696
Your hearing's tomorrow?

244
00:19:58,114 --> 00:20:00,699
I was debating it for a while,
so I'm a little late.

245
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:01,784
I see.

246
00:20:02,493 --> 00:20:04,869
You got a suspended sentence
in the first trial.

247
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:07,163
The charge was injury, not assault.

248
00:20:07,164 --> 00:20:08,374
Sentence in April...

249
00:20:09,417 --> 00:20:10,418
was suspended.

250
00:20:11,669 --> 00:20:14,546
Why appeal when you admitted
to everything in the first trial?

251
00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:17,257
The truth is, I didn't hit him.

252
00:20:17,258 --> 00:20:18,925
Then, why did you admit to it?

253
00:20:18,926 --> 00:20:20,511
I didn't want it to blow up.

254
00:20:24,682 --> 00:20:27,892
It felt like the court was siding
with the other person anyway.

255
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:30,228
So I just admitted it
to wrap things up quickly.

256
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:32,356
I also had to get back to work.

257
00:20:36,569 --> 00:20:40,572
Mr. Park Kyunghyeon, are you a celebrity?
I'm not really familiar.

258
00:20:40,573 --> 00:20:42,074
No, not at all.

259
00:20:42,825 --> 00:20:43,826
No.

260
00:20:44,535 --> 00:20:45,953
I wouldn't say that.

261
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:49,331
Then, what exactly were you afraid
